('697946d4-1af7-4ebc-9bd3-6f700bb75bb8', 'App\\Notifications\\Educator\\NewJobPost', 13, 'App\\User', '{\"job\":{\"title\":\"VWCC Adjunct Faculty: Chemistry\",\"job_type_id\":\"284\",\"deadline\":null,\"state_id\":\"1\",\"city_id\":\"5\",\"category_id\":\"2\",\"grade_id\":\"194\",\"pay_type\":\"salary\",\"description\":\"Virginia Western, located in the heart of the Blue Ridge Mountains of the Roanoke Valley, is accepting applications for part-time, adjunct, Chemistry faculty positions on a continuous basis in the School of Science, Technology, Engineering and Technology. Adjunct faculty positions are appointed on a course-by-course, semester basis as needed. Responsibilities include teaching developmental and\\/or college-level courses, which may include courses during the day and evening, on weekdays and weekends. Faculty are expected to maintain currency in their teaching disciplines and in trends in community college education. Applications will be received and considered on a continuous basis, as openings occur. Review of applications will begin immediately and will continue until needed positions are filled and\\/or the closing date of our announcement.\",\"education\":\"The successful candidate will possess expert skills, knowledge, experience and education in the subject area and a history of successful teaching or related experience. Master\'s in field or Master\'s with 18 graduate semester hours in the teaching field. All Adjunct Faculty positions require excellent oral, written and interpersonal communication skills, experience writing syllabi and exams, as well as the ability to work with students of varying abilities from diverse backgrounds.\",\"skills\":\"Unofficial transcripts of all college coursework completed may be provided as part of the application process. However, official transcripts are required of the selected candidate. Applicants who have degrees earned from educational institutions located outside of the United States are required to ha