('b7720c2b-f135-4d75-bc39-9c5fea0cd6d8', 'App\\Notifications\\Educator\\NewJobPost', 14, 'App\\User', '{\"job\":{\"title\":\"Early Intervention Service Coordinator\",\"job_type_id\":\"284\",\"deadline\":null,\"state_id\":\"1\",\"city_id\":\"4\",\"category_id\":\"7\",\"grade_id\":\"199\",\"pay_type\":\"salary\",\"description\":\"Rewarding position providing quality case management and developmental education services to children from birth to age three with developmental delays and disabilities.\\r\\nDevelop, coordinate, and provide services in the child\\u2019s natural environment as listed in the Individualized Family Service Plan. Document and provide services in compliance with federal and state early intervention guidelines and procedures.  \\r\\nLink families with community resources and work with other professionals to ensure successful completion of developmental outcomes.\",\"education\":\"This position requires excellent interpersonal skills, experience documenting service delivery and a broad knowledge of child development. \\r\\nExperience working with children with disabilities and working with children in their natural environments is desirable. \\r\\nLCSW, LPC or the following teaching licensure preferred: PreK-3, NK-4, PreK-6, or endorsement in special education birth-5.\",\"skills\":\"This position requires excellent interpersonal skills, experience documenting service delivery and a broad knowledge of child development. This position requires excellent interpersonal skills, experience documenting service delivery and a broad knowledge of child development.\",\"additional_information\":\"Link families with community resources and work with other professionals to ensure successful completion of developmental outcomes.\",\"user_id\":2,\"pay_min\":\"40000\",\"pay_max\":\"50000\",\"updated_at\":\"2017-06-26 05:52:36\",\"created_at\":\"2017-06-26 05:52:36\",\"id\":1,\"state\":{\"id\":1,\"name\":\"Texas\",\"short_name\":\"TX\",\"created_at\":\"2017-06-26 0